>The duct tape wasn't cutting it.

I'd never admit that. :-)

>Foam seal has a smooth side and a rough side. I'm guessing  smooth side down?

Yes.

>Where should the ends meet? I'm thinking at the far back top since
>that will have the coolest air when moving. Is that correct?

It doesn't matter as long as there is no gap above the muffler. Because of this folks prefer to start at the back so if there is a gap you only have to fit the seal once. The stock orientation:

